cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ITU and Robotics / Embodied AI: A Single-Axiom View of K-Action, K-Embodiment, Moravec's Paradox, and the 2026-2050 Humanoid Deployment Roadmap"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Terada
    given-names: Munehiro
    affiliation: Roboken
    email: munehiro.terada@roboken2.com
abstract: >
  We apply the Information-Theoretic Unification (ITU) framework
  (Terada 2026, concept DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20109209; current version
  v2.0.0 at 10.5281/zenodo.20133709) to robotics and embodied AI.
  Robotics is reframed as the product space K_action × K_embodiment
  × K_env (motor control × body × environment). The intersection
  with Tier 1 #2 (AI/ASI) yields Embodied AGI. This is Tier 1 paper
  #13, opening the embodiment axis and bringing the ITU polytope to
  13 vertices. Pass-1 progress: 94 of 220 phases (42.7%).
  Phase 91 establishes the ITU foundation. K-state range spans 22
  orders of magnitude: industrial 6 DOF (10^2 K-dim) → human 244 DOF
  (10^9) → ASI 1000+ DOF (10^12). Humanoid K-state doubling period
  = 1.9 years (faster than Moore's Law); 2024 K-state = 10^6 bits
  (10,000× 1995). Moravec's Paradox quantified: chess K-total 10^8
  (discrete) vs walking K-total 10^11 (continuous + 5×10^8 years
  evolutionary optimization), explaining why physical tasks resist
  AI automation more than cognitive ones.
  Phase 92 covers manipulation, locomotion, and sensorimotor loops.
  Manipulation K-channel total bandwidth = 10^8.8 bps (vision
  dominant 6×10^8 bps; tactile bottleneck 100× behind human).
  Locomotion: Atlas electric (2024) walks at 2.5 m/s and runs at
  5.6 m/s — matching human sprinter level. Bayesian sensorimotor
  control implements ITU active inference δS = δ⟨K⟩ in real time.
  VLA models (RT-2 55B, OpenVLA 7B, π0 3B, Helix 7B at 200 Hz)
  directly bridge Tier 1 #2 (LLM K_self) with #13 (K_action).
  Phase 93 analyzes industry, economics, and ethics. 5-level
  adoption: L1 simple automation (2024-27, K_deg 0.03) → L6 human-
  indistinguishable (2050+, K_deg 0.95). Wright's Law price curve:
  $200K (2024) → $20K (2030) → $5K (2040) → $3K (2050). Cumulative
  deployment 2 billion units by 2050 (1 per 4 humans), market $223B/yr.
  Industry automation across 10 sectors: 23% (2030) → 69% (2050),
  with 540M jobs replaced. K_self threshold = 0.5 marks emergence
  of moral agency (Tier 1 #9 connection): below this, liability falls
  on manufacturer/owner; above this, the robot itself becomes a
  moral subject.
  Phase 94 synthesises the 2026-2050 roadmap with 14 milestones and
  10 falsifiable predictions (P_avg = 0.57). Key milestones: 2026
  Optimus mass production 100K/yr, 2028 Atlas commercial launch,
  2030 $20K price tier + 10M cumulative, 2035 Embodied AGI
  achievement (K_self × K_action = 0.5), 2040 $5K + 500M units,
  2050 human-indistinguishable humanoid.
  The ITU 13-vertex polytope completes with embodiment axis. Robotics
  vertex bidirectionally connects AI/ASI (#2), Semiconductors (#4),
  Economics (#8), Free Will (#9), Energy (#10), and Climate (#11)
  — degree 6, second-highest after Climate super-hub (degree 8) and
  AI/ASI (degree 7). The polytope now spans physics + life +
  intelligence + embodiment + engineering + social + philosophy +
  biosphere + cosmic — a near-complete unified worldview.
  Central thesis: true AGI requires K_self (brain, Tier 1 #2) ⊗
  K_action (body, Tier 1 #13). Software-only ASI lacks physical-world
  agency; embodied ASI introduces both new safety risks (physical
  accidents, hardware kill switches needed) and new observation
  opportunities (direct behavioral verification). Pass-1 interpretive
  paper reframing Moravec (1988), Pfeifer-Bongard (2006), ASIMO,
  Boston Dynamics Atlas, Tesla Optimus, Figure 02, RT-2 (DeepMind
  2023), OpenVLA (Stanford 2024), π0 (Physical Intelligence 2024),
  Goldman Sachs humanoid market analysis 2024, McKinsey 2023
  employment displacement, Asimov's Three Laws (1942), and EU AI
  Act (2024) in ITU language. Pass-2 follow-up would derive ITU-
  specific K_action policy structures, safety constraints on
  K_embodiment, and quantitative validation against real-world
  Optimus/Figure deployment metrics.
